		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />After rereading the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC1" class="postlink">the wiki's &quot;MMC1 technical reference&quot;</a>:<br /><br /><ul><li>MMC1 always has an 8kb PRG-RAM bank at $6000-$7FFF </li><li>This bank is switchable in only SOROM and SXROM. </li><li>When using SOROM or SXROM, you actually have 32kbs of PRG-RAM in banks 0 through 3.</li></ul><br />That's true right?  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br />1.)  I don't know how to switch the PRG-RAM banks.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarassed" /> How does one accomplish that?  Thought it would be cool if you could use bit4 to switch between setting bank of PRG-ROM or PRG-RAM, but it is used for something else:<div class="quotetitle"><span style="color: #8040FF">nesdev wiki's MMC1 technical reference</span> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><strong>PRG bank (internal, $E000-$FFFF)</strong><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;4bit0<br />&nbsp;-----<br />&nbsp;RPPPP<br />&nbsp;|||||<br />&nbsp;|++++- Select 16 KB PRG ROM bank (low bit ignored in 32 KB mode)<br />&nbsp;+----- PRG RAM chip enable (0: enabled; 1: disabled; ignored on MMC1A)</div></div><br /><br />2.) How would you set a game to use SOROM or SXROM? <br /><br />Those are two questions that seem unsolvable to just me. Right now, 8kb of PRG-RAM seems like a continent of space to me; but, I think, having access to 4 continents wouldn't be a hindrance. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

